        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued June 4 at 7:08PM MDT by NWS Denver CO</headline>
        <description>At 708 PM MDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm near
Fort Lupton, or 20 miles south of Greeley, moving north at 10 mph.

HAZARD...Penny size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Minor damage to outdoor objects and vegetation is possible.

Locations impacted include...
Firestone, Fort Lupton and Platteville.
</description>
        <instruction>Monitor the weather situation closely and be alert for threatening
weather conditions.</instruction>
